    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-15T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="479"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d479">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851R.01/49a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Under Secretary of State (<persName type="from"
                            >Welles</persName>) to President <persName type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-15">December 15,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. President</hi>: With reference to the message
                    which Admiral Leahy delivered to me from you this afternoon, I am transmitting
                    herewith the suggested message to be sent by the War Department to General
                    Eisenhower.</p>
                <p>If this meets with your approval<note n="5" xml:id="d479fn5">Approved by
                        President Roosevelt.</note> I shall arrange to have it sent off by the War
                    Department as soon as possible.</p>
                <p>Believe me</p>
                <p>Faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sumner Welles</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <pb facs="0488" n="482" xml:id="pg_482"/>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Enclosure]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Draft of Telegram To Be Sent by the <gloss type="from">War
                                Department</gloss> to General <persName type="to"
                                >Eisenhower</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </head>
                    <p>“I am today appointing Mr. Murphy to be my personal representative in North
                        Africa with the rank of Minister. He will continue on General Eisenhower’s
                        staff in his present capacity as Civil Affairs Officer until such a time as
                        consultation with the War Department suggests a change.</p>
                    <p>“The British Government is being informed in the above sense today.”</p>
                    <closer>
                        <dateline rendition="#left">
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-15">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">December</hi> 15, 1942</date>.</dateline>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
